SIMPLE: thirteenth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thirteenth
<hw>Thir"teenth`</hw> <pr>(th⟦etil⟧r"t⟦emac⟧nth`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[From <er>Thirteen</er>: cf. AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧re⟦oacute⟧te⟦oacute⟧⟦edh⟧a</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Next in order after the twelfth; the third after the tenth; -- the
ordinal of <xex>thirteen</xex>; <as>as, the <ex>thirteenth</ex> day of
the month</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Constituting or being one of thirteen equal parts
into which anything is divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thirteenth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thirteenth
<hw>Thir"teenth`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quotient of a
unit divided by thirteen; one of thirteen equal parts into which
anything is divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The next in order after the twelfth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The interval comprising an octave
and a sixth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thirtieth</ent>⟦br⟧
